---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const personSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Person',
  name: 'Jonathan Malkin',
  jobTitle: 'AI Workflow Consultant & Implementation Partner',
  description: 'Jonathan Malkin audits one workflow at a time, finds where AI can safely help, and either builds it on your platform or runs a hands-on workshop so your team builds it themselves.',
  url: 'https://builtwithjon.com',
  sameAs: [
    'https://github.com/jonathanmalkin',
    'https://x.com/builtwithjon',
    'https://linkedin.com/in/jonathanmalkin',
  ],
};

const websiteSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'WebSite',
  name: 'Jonathan Malkin',
  url: 'https://builtwithjon.com',
  description: 'Start with an AI workflow audit: map one process, find where AI can safely help, then have it built for you or build it with your team.',
};
---

<Base
  title="Jonathan Malkin"
  description="Start with an AI workflow audit: map one process, find where AI can safely help, then have it built for you or build it with your team."
  schema={personSchema}
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(websiteSchema)} />

  <section class="hero-split container-wide">
    <div class="hero-split-copy">
      <p class="eyebrow">Start with the AI workflow audit</p>
      <h1>Find the one workflow AI should actually help with.</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">
        Bring one recurring process that costs you time, follow-up, or trust. I map it, find where AI can safely help, and hand you a first pilot plan you can act on. From there you can have it built or build it with your team.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-links">
        <a href="/ai-workflow-audit/" class="hero-btn">Start with an audit</a>
        <a href="/use-cases/" class="hero-btn-outline">See the use case library &rarr;</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <figure class="hero-split-media">
      <img
        src="/home/workshop-room.jpg"
        width="1600"
        height="900"
        alt="A full room of people watching Jonathan present a live AI demo on screen at AI Tinkerers in Sao Paulo."
        loading="eager"
        decoding="async"
      />
      <figcaption>Live demo at AI Tinkerers, Sao Paulo</figcaption>
    </figure>
  </section>

  <section class="container offerings" style="margin-bottom: 3rem;" aria-labelledby="offerings-h">
    <p class="eyebrow">Work with me</p>
    <h2 id="offerings-h">One workflow at a time.</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">
      No big platform decision, no pricing puzzle. We map one real process you run today, then decide together if it is worth going further.
    </p>

    <a href="/ai-workflow-audit/" class="offer-frontdoor">
      <span class="offer-frontdoor-label">The front door</span>
      <span class="offer-frontdoor-title">The AI workflow audit &rarr;</span>
      <span class="offer-frontdoor-desc">Bring one recurring process. I map it, find where AI can safely help, and hand you a first pilot plan. The write-up is yours to keep whether or not we work together again.</span>
    </a>

    <p class="offer-split-intro">Then, if it earns the next step, two ways forward:</p>
    <div class="offer-routes">
      <div class="offer-route">
        <span class="offer-route-label">Have it done for you</span>
        <h3>I build it on your platform</h3>
        <p>I implement the pilot in the tools you already use, Claude Cowork or Google Workspace, so you own it from day one. Nothing of mine to host. After the build I can stay on in an advisory or fractional role.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="offer-route">
        <span class="offer-route-label">Build the capability</span>
        <h3>Your team builds it, in a workshop</h3>
        <p>A hands-on session where your people build the real thing against your own work, with human approval gates so it never acts on its own. They walk out able to run and extend it themselves.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container how-i-work" style="margin-bottom: 3rem;" aria-labelledby="how-i-work-h">
    <p class="eyebrow">How I work</p>
    <h2 id="how-i-work-h">A method, not a tool pitch.</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">
      Before any build, the same approach every time: connect the data, audit the workflow not the tool, and keep a human at the high-stakes gate. It's all public.
    </p>
    <div class="method-links">
      <a href="/principles/" class="method-card">
        <span class="method-eyebrow">The beliefs</span>
        <span class="method-title">Principles &rarr;</span>
        <span class="method-desc">Five rules every automation runs through.</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/process/" class="method-card">
        <span class="method-eyebrow">The sequence</span>
        <span class="method-title">Process &rarr;</span>
        <span class="method-desc">The five phases from "here's my mess" to a working system.</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/use-cases/" class="method-card">
        <span class="method-eyebrow">The proof</span>
        <span class="method-title">Use case library &rarr;</span>
        <span class="method-desc">96 worked examples across 15 kinds of business.</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container why-me-grid" style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
    <div>
      <h2>Why me</h2>
      <p class="cred-line">
        20+ years in enterprise tech, spent getting teams to actually adopt new systems, not just buy them. I run my own AI workflows every day, so what I build and teach is what I already use.
      </p>
      <p><a href="/about/">More about how I work &rarr;</a></p>
    </div>
    <figure class="why-me-media">
      <img
        src="/home/jules-demo.jpg"
        width="1400"
        height="787"
        alt="Close view of a live AI assistant demo on screen, showing the presenter alongside a real-time AI avatar."
        loading="lazy"
        decoding="async"
      />
    </figure>
  </section>

  <section class="container home-final-cta">
    <p class="eyebrow">Let's talk</p>
    <h2>Want AI doing real work, not just talked about?</h2>
    <p>
      Tell me about one workflow that is slowing you down. I will tell you whether it is worth an audit, and where AI should stay out.
    </p>
    <div class="hero-links" style="justify-content: center;">
      <a href="/ai-workflow-audit/" class="hero-btn">Start with an audit</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
